cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with mammographic mass segmentation using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also employs adversarial training to eliminate over-fitting, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with medical imaging, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also employs a fully convolutional network (FCN) and a conditional random field (CRF), which are common techniques in artificial intelligence, falling under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper employs multi-scale FCN, which is a neural network architecture, falling under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
